claim.claim-text:
19. A wireless location assist device (WLAD), comprising:
a non-AC power source;
control logic operable from the non-AC power source;
a wireless radio coupled to the control logic and operable from the non-AC power source;
wherein the control logic causes the radio to transmit wireless local area network (WLAN) beacons across a wireless medium without sensing the wireless medium before transmitting each beacon;
wherein the control logic initiates a sleep mode after transmitting each beacon; and
wherein the control logic never responds to an authentication request from a wireless station so as to not permit the WLAD to associate with wireless stations.
